  "serviceNotes": {
    "brake fluid": "Brake fluid is hygroscopic and absorbs moisture over time, reducing its boiling point and braking effectiveness. Replacement is time-based, not distance-based — typically every 2 years regardless of mileage.",
    "check front brake pads": "BMW CBS-style pad inspection; 30,000 km is a reasonable cadence between major services. Strong regen on i3 BEV often extends front pad life.",
    "check rear brake pads": "BMW CBS-style pad inspection; 30,000 km is a reasonable cadence between major services. Strong regen on i3 BEV often extends rear pad life.",
    "coolant flush": "High-voltage battery and e-drive cooling circuit: BMW publishes time/distance-based coolant service for EVs; 60,000 km is a planning proxy—interval estimated, confirm official service data. Range Extender (REx) models additionally require petrol engine oil, spark plugs, and air filter per the REx supplement—follow BMW i service data.",
    "gearbox fluid": "Reduction gear / drive unit fluid: officially often \"lifetime\"; 100,000 km mfr row is interval estimated for long-term wear metals in oil—specialist preventive change.",
    "micro filter": "Microfilter per BMW i maintenance programme; 20,000 km planning interval—verify display and regional booklet."
  },
